# semgrep ignore list — paths skipped during `semgrep scan`.
#
# Pinned in T-061 (Harness A4). Active scope is `api/app/` only (per
# `.github/workflows/pr.yml` security job invocation); the directives
# below mostly defend against developers running `semgrep` from the repo
# root and getting drowned in vendored / generated-file noise.
#
# Adding an ignore here is permanent for that path — for individual rule
# suppressions inside scanned code, prefer the inline `# nosemgrep:
# <rule-id>  # reason` comment so the carve-out is co-located with the
# code it justifies.

# ── Generated / vendored ────────────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
.venv/
venv/
dist/
build/
.next/
*.egg-info/

# ── Test code ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# pytest fixtures intentionally exercise dangerous code paths (assert
# everywhere, fakeredis with no auth, fake JWTs, etc.) — scanning them
# produces noise that drowns out real findings in production paths. Same
# rationale as `[tool.bandit] exclude_dirs = ["tests"]` in pyproject.toml.
api/tests/
web/tests/
web/playwright-report/
web/test-results/

# ── Alembic auto-generated migrations ───────────────────────────────────
# Autogen output mirrors ORM column types and frequently includes
# string-concatenated SQL fragments that semgrep flags as injection
# candidates. The patterns are SQLAlchemy-templated, not user-driven.
api/alembic/versions/

# ── Mutation testing sandbox (T-060) ────────────────────────────────────
# `mutmut run` writes a per-mutant copy of the codebase here. Scanning
# it would re-flag every finding once per mutant.
api/mutants/

# ── Stub fixtures (binary / image assets) ───────────────────────────────
api/app/ai/_fixtures/

# ── Frontend ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOT listed here on purpose. The CI invocation in `.github/workflows/pr.yml`
# scopes semgrep to `api/app/`, so `web/` is already unreachable — listing
# it would falsely imply "we scanned frontend then suppressed". Frontend
# SAST is deferred per T-061 §"Not in scope"; when that ticket lands, the
# scope expands by editing the CI command (and possibly adding directory
# carve-outs here), not by dropping entries from this file.
